HEADWORD: Rheocrat
<hw>Rhe"o*crat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"rei^n</grk> to flow + <grk>kratei^n</grk> to rule.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A kind of motor speed controller permitting of
very gradual variation in speed and of reverse. It is especially
suitable for use with motor driven machine tools.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rheometer</ent>⟦br⟧
